//@version=6
// =====================================================================================
// TVB-EXP Champion [TVB-12r]        v2 -- champion-search harness, hardened collector echo
// v2 (TVB-12, audit F1 remediation): adds a collector nonce input (echoed in the METRICS
//   table -- a report is only accepted when the echoed nonce matches the inputs just
//   applied, causally binding report to configuration) plus chart_tf / session / bf_tf /
//   bf_strength echo rows. Trading logic UNCHANGED from v1 (incl. the conditional 60m BF
//   guard fix); all v2 additions are display-only. Tables draw on islastconfirmedhistory
//   as well as islast (realtime-bar fix -- the TVB-11 echo flakiness root cause).
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Pre-registration: docs/experiments/tvb11_champion_prereg.md (APPROVED 2026-07-14).
// Base = TVB-EXP BF Exit [Claude] v2 (pine/tvb_exp_bf_exit.pine), byte-compatible in
// behavior for recycle/ratchet_c cells on 24/7 perps, with exactly three P1 changes:
//   1) bf_reentry gains 'ratchet_g' -- verbatim port of the GPT arming-gate variant
//      (single shared block slot; entry allowed only when the NATURAL trigger stands
//      strictly beyond the running post-exit extreme; the stop is never raised).
//      ratchet_c stays the raised-stop variant (independent per-side blocks; stop =
//      max(natural trigger, extreme + tick)). See pre-reg Section 3.
//   2) Session-robust period clocks: arm/exit period closes detected with
//      time_close == time_close(tf) instead of wall-clock modulo. The modulo idiom is
//      correct on 24/7 UTC perps but NEVER fires on RTH charts whose intraday periods
//      end off the hour (NYSE 60m closes 10:30, 11:30, ...). Equivalence on perps is
//      proven by anchor check P3 before any grid run.
//   3) Machine-readable collector echo (GPT-proven method): transparent METRICS table
//      (full cell echo + results + loaded window) and TRADES table (per-trade rows
//      incl. size, profit(), commission, and computed slippage-adjusted GROSS -- the
//      P0b closedtrades.profit() gross-vs-net polarity probe). A run is REJECTED by
//      the collector unless the echoed cell matches the requested cell.
// Entry engine = intrabar-armed breakout: live 6-TF gate (close vs current period
//   open, unanimous), breakout stop at the prior COMPLETED arm_tf bar extreme +/- 1
//   tick (strict break, closed setup bar), in force only while the live gate is
//   aligned+permitted. Regime stand_aside + TVB-6 loss-ratchet governor retained.
// Native exits  = decided at exit_tf closes (state | flip), fill at next open.
// BF exits      = resting orders at the projected broadening line for the NEXT bar.
// BF engine     = verbatim BF-1 port (fractal pivots via completed-bar [1] +
//   lookahead_on security idiom -- non-repainting by construction, audited).
// Gate fidelity = NO request.security for the gate; local period-open reconstruction.
// Known deltas vs the Companion display (disclosed, shared by all cells):
//   orders placed on bar N fill from bar N+1; historical intrabar granularity is
//   chart-TF-grade; a BF line that validates and deviates on the SAME bar is missed.
// =====================================================================================

strategy('TVB-EXP Champion [TVB-12r]', 'CHAMP', overlay = true,
     initial_capital = 10000,
     default_qty_type = strategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_value = 100,
     commission_type = strategy.commission.percent, commission_value = 0.0125,
     slippage = 1, margin_long = 0, margin_short = 0,
     use_bar_magnifier = true, max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500)

// ----------------------------------- Inputs -----------------------------------
var string g_exp = 'EXPERIMENT CELL (swept by the collector)'
exit_mode = input.string('flip', 'Exit mode', options = ['state', 'flip'], group = g_exp, tooltip = 'Native exit. state: exit at the first exit-TF close where the gate is no longer FULLY aligned with the position (grey exits). flip: exit only on full OPPOSITE alignment (holds through grey).')
bf_exit   = input.string('off', 'BF exit', options = ['off', 'same_side', 'any_side'], group = g_exp, tooltip = 'Broadening-formation deviation exit, racing the native exit (first fill wins). off: native exit only. same_side: exhaustion harvest -- long exits at the UPPER line (sell limit), short at the LOWER line (buy limit). any_side: same_side plus the adverse line as a protective stop (grid restricts this to recycle).')
bf_reentry = input.string('recycle', 'BF re-entry', options = ['recycle', 'ratchet_c', 'ratchet_g'], group = g_exp, tooltip = 'What happens after a BF exit. recycle: nothing blocks re-entry -- if the gate is still aligned the next breakout re-enters immediately. ratchet_c (raised stop, Claude E2): re-entry stop is RAISED to strictly beyond the most extreme price since the BF exit; fires the first tick beyond; independent per-side blocks. ratchet_g (arming gate, GPT E2): the stop is never moved -- no order rests until the NATURAL arm-TF trigger itself stands strictly beyond the running extreme; single shared block slot (an opposite-side BF exit overwrites it). Both clear on the re-entry fill or on full opposite alignment at an exit-TF close. Never report "ratchet" without the suffix.')

var string g_tf = 'Clocks: arming TF, exit TF, gate TFs'
arm_tf  = input.timeframe('15', 'Arming TF (entry trigger structure)', group = g_tf, tooltip = 'Which prior COMPLETED bar extreme the breakout stop rests at (+/- 1 tick). Must be >= the chart TF, a multiple of it, and tile the Exit TF.')
exit_tf = input.timeframe('15', 'Exit TF (exit decision clock)', group = g_tf, tooltip = 'The clock exits commit on: the state/flip condition is evaluated at THIS TF closes (from the last chart bar of each period) and the exit fills at the next chart bar open. Also the governor and BF-block alignment-reset clock. Must be intraday, tiled by the Arming TF, and tile every gate TF.')
y1  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '1', group = g_tf)
tf1 = input.timeframe('60', 'TF 1', inline = '1', group = g_tf)
y2  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '2', group = g_tf)
tf2 = input.timeframe('120', 'TF 2', inline = '2', group = g_tf)
y3  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '3', group = g_tf)
tf3 = input.timeframe('240', 'TF 3', inline = '3', group = g_tf)
y4  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '4', group = g_tf)
tf4 = input.timeframe('D', 'TF 4', inline = '4', group = g_tf)
y5  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '5', group = g_tf)
tf5 = input.timeframe('W', 'TF 5', inline = '5', group = g_tf)
y6  = input.bool(true, '', inline = '6', group = g_tf)
tf6 = input.timeframe('M', 'TF 6', inline = '6', group = g_tf)

var string g_dir = 'Direction'
allow_long  = input.bool(true, 'Allow Long', group = g_dir)
allow_short = input.bool(true, 'Allow Short', group = g_dir)

var string g_reg = 'Regime layer (A1 fixed: stand_aside on W+D)'
reg_mode = input.string('stand_aside', 'Regime mode', options = ['off', 'stand_aside'], group = g_reg)
rg1  = input.bool(false, '', inline = 'r1', group = g_reg)
rtf1 = input.timeframe('M', 'Regime TF 1', inline = 'r1', group = g_reg)
rg2  = input.bool(true, '', inline = 'r2', group = g_reg)
rtf2 = input.timeframe('W', 'Regime TF 2', inline = 'r2', group = g_reg)
rg3  = input.bool(true, '', inline = 'r3', group = g_reg)
rtf3 = input.timeframe('D', 'Regime TF 3', inline = 'r3', group = g_reg)

var string g_gov = 'Re-entry governor (TVB-6 loss ratchet; A1 fixed: ratchet)'
gov_mode = input.string('ratchet', 'Governor mode', options = ['off', 'ratchet'], group = g_gov)

var string g_bf = 'Broadening Formation engine'
string bf_tf = input.timeframe('30', 'BF pivot timeframe', group = g_bf, tooltip = 'Timeframe the fractal pivots and broadening lines are built from.')
int bf_strength = input.int(10, 'BF pivot strength (pivot-TF bars)', minval = 1, maxval = 50, group = g_bf, tooltip = 'Pivot confirmation lag = strength x pivot TF BY DEFINITION.')
bool bf_show_pivots = input.bool(false, 'Show BF pivot dots', group = g_bf)

var string g_viz = 'Display'
show_table = input.bool(true, 'Cell/status table', group = g_viz)
show_trig  = input.bool(true, 'Working entry trigger dots', group = g_viz)
// MUST stay the LAST input: the collector's input-id map depends on declaration order.
coll_nonce = input.string('', 'Collector nonce (blank for manual use)', group = g_viz, tooltip = 'Set per-run by the batch collector and echoed back in the METRICS table. The collector only accepts a report whose echoed nonce matches the one it just applied, so a stale report can never be attributed to a new configuration. No effect on trading.')

// ------------- Guards: chart tiles arm_tf; arm_tf tiles exit_tf; exit_tf tiles gates -------------
f_guard(simple string base_name, simple int base_s, simple string tf, simple bool enabled) =>
    if enabled
        gs = timeframe.in_seconds(tf)
        if gs < base_s
            runtime.error('TF "' + tf + '" is finer than ' + base_name + '. It must be >= and tiled by it.')
        if gs >= 86400
            if 86400 % base_s != 0
                runtime.error(base_name + ' does not divide 1D -- D/W/M period-open reconstruction would be approximate.')
        else if gs % base_s != 0
            runtime.error('TF "' + tf + '" is not an integer multiple of ' + base_name + ' -- reconstruction would be approximate.')

chart_s = timeframe.in_seconds(timeframe.period)
arm_s   = timeframe.in_seconds(arm_tf)
exit_s  = timeframe.in_seconds(exit_tf)
if exit_s >= 86400
    runtime.error('CHAMP: Exit TF must be intraday (< 1D) -- the last-bar-of-period exit clock needs it.')
if arm_s >= 86400
    runtime.error('CHAMP: Arming TF must be intraday (< 1D).')
f_guard('the chart TF (' + timeframe.period + ')', chart_s, arm_tf, true)
f_guard('the Arming TF (' + arm_tf + ')', arm_s, exit_tf, true)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf1, y1)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf2, y2)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf3, y3)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf4, y4)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf5, y5)
f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, tf6, y6)
if reg_mode != 'off'
    f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, rtf1, rg1)
    f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, rtf2, rg2)
    f_guard('the Exit TF (' + exit_tf + ')', exit_s, rtf3, rg3)

int bf_sec = timeframe.in_seconds(bf_tf)
// Guard fires only when the BF engine is actually IN USE: with bf_exit = 'off' the
// engine's outputs feed nothing (no exit orders, no re-entry blocks), so a BF TF
// below the chart TF is harmless there. An unconditional guard killed every
// 60m-chart cell of the A1 grid including BF-off ones (found mid-grid 2026-07-14).
if bf_exit != 'off' and bf_sec < chart_s
    runtime.error('CHAMP: BF pivot timeframe (' + bf_tf + ') is below the chart TF -- BF exits cannot run here.')
bool bf_use_sec = bf_sec > chart_s

max_bars_back(time, 4900)
max_bars_back(high, 4900)
max_bars_back(low, 4900)

// ------------- Gate (FTFC): LOCAL period-open reconstruction (TVB-3 fix) -------------
f_open(simple string tf) =>
    ta.valuewhen(timeframe.change(tf), open, 0)

o1 = f_open(tf1)
o2 = f_open(tf2)
o3 = f_open(tf3)
o4 = f_open(tf4)
o5 = f_open(tf5)
o6 = f_open(tf6)

use_arr  = array.from(y1, y2, y3, y4, y5, y6)
open_arr = array.from(o1, o2, o3, o4, o5, o6)

ftfc_up = true
ftfc_dn = true
int n_enabled = 0
for i = 0 to array.size(use_arr) - 1 by 1
    if array.get(use_arr, i)
        n_enabled += 1
        op = array.get(open_arr, i)
        if close > op
            ftfc_dn := false
        else if close < op
            ftfc_up := false
        else
            ftfc_up := false
            ftfc_dn := false
if n_enabled == 0
    ftfc_up := false
    ftfc_dn := false

// ------------------------------- Regime layer -------------------------------
f_agg(u_arr, o_arr) =>
    up = true
    dn = true
    int n = 0
    for i = 0 to array.size(u_arr) - 1 by 1
        if array.get(u_arr, i)
            n += 1
            op = array.get(o_arr, i)
            if close > op
                dn := false
            else if close < op
                up := false
            else
                up := false
                dn := false
    if n == 0
        up := false
        dn := false
    [up, dn]

ro1 = f_open(rtf1)
ro2 = f_open(rtf2)
ro3 = f_open(rtf3)
[reg_up, reg_dn] = f_agg(array.from(rg1, rg2, rg3), array.from(ro1, ro2, ro3))

long_permit  = reg_mode == 'off' ? true : reg_up
short_permit = reg_mode == 'off' ? true : reg_dn

// ------------- Clocks: arming structure (arm_tf) + exit decisions (exit_tf) -------------
// P1 change 2: SESSION-ROBUST period-close detection. The last chart bar of a period
// on tf satisfies time_close == time_close(tf) on BOTH 24/7 UTC perps and RTH session
// charts (whose intraday periods end off the wall-clock hour). The wall-clock modulo
// idiom of the E2 base script is retired. Perp-equivalence is proven by anchor P3.
arm_new   = timeframe.change(arm_tf)
arm_last  = time_close == time_close(arm_tf)
exit_last = time_close == time_close(exit_tf)

var float a_high   = na
var float a_low    = na
var float prev_ah  = na     // prior COMPLETED arm_tf bar extremes = trigger structure
var float prev_al  = na

if arm_new
    a_high := high
    a_low := low
else
    a_high := na(a_high) ? high : math.max(a_high, high)
    a_low := na(a_low) ? low : math.min(a_low, low)

if arm_last
    prev_ah := a_high
    prev_al := a_low

// ------------- Governor + BF re-entry block state -------------
var float ratchet_long  = na
var float ratchet_short = na
var float pend_trig_l   = na
var float pend_trig_s   = na
var float trig_l_used   = na
var float trig_s_used   = na
var int   closed_cnt    = 0
var float bf_block_l    = na    // ratchet_c: per-side post-BF-exit block levels (running extremes)
var float bf_block_s    = na
var int   bf_g_dir      = 0     // ratchet_g: single shared slot (+1 blocks longs, -1 blocks shorts)
var float bf_g_ext      = na

// ratchet_c: running extremes while a block is active (price since the BF exit)
if not na(bf_block_l)
    bf_block_l := math.max(bf_block_l, high)
if not na(bf_block_s)
    bf_block_s := math.min(bf_block_s, low)

if strategy.opentrades > 0 and strategy.opentrades[1] == 0
    if strategy.position_size > 0
        trig_l_used := pend_trig_l
        bf_block_l := na          // re-entry filled beyond the block = new evidence; consume it
        if bf_g_dir == 1
            bf_g_dir := 0
            bf_g_ext := na
    else
        trig_s_used := pend_trig_s
        bf_block_s := na
        if bf_g_dir == -1
            bf_g_dir := 0
            bf_g_ext := na

if strategy.closedtrades > closed_cnt
    for i = closed_cnt to strategy.closedtrades - 1
        bool was_long = strategy.closedtrades.size(i) > 0
        if was_long
            ratchet_long := strategy.closedtrades.profit(i) > 0 ? na : trig_l_used
        else
            ratchet_short := strategy.closedtrades.profit(i) > 0 ? na : trig_s_used
        // only BF exits arm a re-entry block (exit comments start with 'BF')
        if str.startswith(strategy.closedtrades.exit_comment(i), 'BF')
            if bf_reentry == 'ratchet_c'
                if was_long
                    bf_block_l := high
                else
                    bf_block_s := low
            if bf_reentry == 'ratchet_g'
                bf_g_dir := was_long ? 1 : -1
                bf_g_ext := was_long ? high : low
    closed_cnt := strategy.closedtrades

// ratchet_g: running extreme advances on every chart bar while the block is active
// (GPT source ordering: update AFTER fill/closed-trade bookkeeping, same bar included)
if bf_g_dir == 1
    bf_g_ext := na(bf_g_ext) ? high : math.max(bf_g_ext, high)
else if bf_g_dir == -1
    bf_g_ext := na(bf_g_ext) ? low : math.min(bf_g_ext, low)

// ------------- Native exit + alignment resets, at exit_tf closes -------------
if exit_last
    if ftfc_dn
        ratchet_long := na
        bf_block_l := na          // full opposite alignment ends the episode (mirror governor)
        if bf_g_dir == 1
            bf_g_dir := 0
            bf_g_ext := na
    if ftfc_up
        ratchet_short := na
        bf_block_s := na
        if bf_g_dir == -1
            bf_g_dir := 0
            bf_g_ext := na
    if strategy.position_size > 0
        if exit_mode == 'flip' ? ftfc_dn : not ftfc_up
            strategy.close('L', comment = 'TFC exit')
    if strategy.position_size < 0
        if exit_mode == 'flip' ? ftfc_up : not ftfc_dn
            strategy.close('S', comment = 'TFC exit')

// ------------- Intrabar-armed entry: revocable stop while the live gate is aligned -------------
float trig_l = prev_ah + syminfo.mintick
float trig_s = prev_al - syminfo.mintick
// ratchet_c: the block RAISES the resting stop -- trigger must clear the post-exit extreme too
float eff_trig_l = not na(bf_block_l) ? math.max(trig_l, bf_block_l + syminfo.mintick) : trig_l
float eff_trig_s = not na(bf_block_s) ? math.min(trig_s, bf_block_s - syminfo.mintick) : trig_s
// ratchet_g: the block GATES arming -- the NATURAL trigger must already stand beyond the extreme
bool bfg_l_ok = bf_reentry != 'ratchet_g' or bf_g_dir != 1 or (not na(trig_l) and trig_l > bf_g_ext)
bool bfg_s_ok = bf_reentry != 'ratchet_g' or bf_g_dir != -1 or (not na(trig_s) and trig_s < bf_g_ext)
bool gov_on  = gov_mode == 'ratchet'
bool gl_ok   = not gov_on or na(ratchet_long) or eff_trig_l > ratchet_long
bool gs_ok   = not gov_on or na(ratchet_short) or eff_trig_s < ratchet_short

var int armed = 0
if strategy.position_size == 0 and not na(prev_ah)
    if allow_long and ftfc_up and long_permit and gl_ok and bfg_l_ok
        strategy.entry('L', strategy.long, stop = eff_trig_l, comment = 'TFC long')
        pend_trig_l := eff_trig_l
        strategy.cancel('S')
        armed := 1
    else if allow_short and ftfc_dn and short_permit and gs_ok and bfg_s_ok
        strategy.entry('S', strategy.short, stop = eff_trig_s, comment = 'TFC short')
        pend_trig_s := eff_trig_s
        strategy.cancel('L')
        armed := -1
    else
        strategy.cancel('L')
        strategy.cancel('S')
        armed := 0
else
    strategy.cancel('L')
    strategy.cancel('S')
    armed := 0

// =====================================================================================
// Broadening Formation engine -- verbatim port of "Broadening Formation MTF [BF-1]" v1
// (pivot storage, pairing, validation, deviation). delete_old fixed to OFF.
// =====================================================================================
f_fractal_hi(int n) =>
    bool acc = true
    for j = -n to n
        if j != 0
            acc := acc and high[n] > high[n + j]
    acc ? high[n] : na

f_fractal_lo(int n) =>
    bool acc = true
    for j = -n to n
        if j != 0
            acc := acc and low[n] < low[n + j]
    acc ? low[n] : na

f_anchor(int t, int cap) =>
    int res = na
    for k = 0 to cap
        if time[k] <= t
            res := bar_index - k
            break
    res

f_push(array<float> af, array<int> ai, float v, int idx) =>
    array.unshift(af, v)
    array.unshift(ai, idx)
    if array.size(af) > 10
        array.pop(af)
        array.pop(ai)

// Non-repaint idiom: completed-bar values ([1]) + lookahead_on.
[s_phv, s_plv, s_pt] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, bf_tf, [f_fractal_hi(bf_strength)[1], f_fractal_lo(bf_strength)[1], time[bf_strength + 1]], lookahead = barmerge.lookahead_on)

float phv = bf_use_sec ? s_phv : f_fractal_hi(bf_strength)
float plv = bf_use_sec ? s_plv : f_fractal_lo(bf_strength)
int   pt  = bf_use_sec ? s_pt : time[bf_strength]

var int last_ph_t = -1
var int last_pl_t = -1

int ratio    = math.max(1, int(math.ceil(bf_sec / float(chart_s))))
int scan_cap = math.min(4800, (bf_strength + 3) * ratio)
int pt_key   = nz(pt, -1)

bool ev_ok  = bf_use_sec or barstate.isconfirmed
bool new_ph = ev_ok and not na(phv) and pt_key > 0 and pt_key != last_ph_t
bool new_pl = ev_ok and not na(plv) and pt_key > 0 and pt_key != last_pl_t

var pivot_highs     = array.new_float()
var pivot_highs_idx = array.new_int()
var pivot_lows      = array.new_float()
var pivot_lows_idx  = array.new_int()

if new_ph
    last_ph_t := pt_key
    int a = f_anchor(pt_key, scan_cap)
    if not na(a) and bar_index - a < 4500
        f_push(pivot_highs, pivot_highs_idx, phv, a)
        if bf_show_pivots
            label.new(a, phv, '.', style = label.style_none, textcolor = color.gray, size = size.tiny)

if new_pl
    last_pl_t := pt_key
    int a = f_anchor(pt_key, scan_cap)
    if not na(a) and bar_index - a < 4500
        f_push(pivot_lows, pivot_lows_idx, plv, a)
        if bf_show_pivots
            label.new(a, plv, '.', style = label.style_none, textcolor = color.gray, size = size.tiny)

var line upper_tl = na
var line lower_tl = na

if (new_ph or new_pl) and array.size(pivot_highs) > 1 and array.size(pivot_lows) > 1
    float low_new = array.get(pivot_lows, 0)
    float low_old = array.get(pivot_lows, 1)
    int   lni     = array.get(pivot_lows_idx, 0)
    int   loi     = array.get(pivot_lows_idx, 1)

    if not na(low_new) and not na(low_old) and low_new < low_old and lni > loi and bar_index - loi < 4800
        float slope = (low_new - low_old) / (lni - loi)
        bool  valid = true
        int   span  = lni - loi
        for i = 0 to span
            if low[bar_index - loi - i] < low_old + slope * i
                valid := false
                break
        if valid
            lower_tl := line.new(loi, low_old, lni, low_new, style = line.style_solid, color = color.gray, width = 1)
            array.set(pivot_lows, 0, na)
            array.set(pivot_lows, 1, na)

    float high_new = array.get(pivot_highs, 0)
    float high_old = array.get(pivot_highs, 1)
    int   hni      = array.get(pivot_highs_idx, 0)
    int   hoi      = array.get(pivot_highs_idx, 1)

    if not na(high_new) and not na(high_old) and high_new > high_old and hni > hoi and bar_index - hoi < 4800
        float slope = (high_new - high_old) / (hni - hoi)
        bool  valid = true
        int   span  = hni - hoi
        for i = 0 to span
            if high[bar_index - hoi - i] > high_old + slope * i
                valid := false
                break
        if valid
            upper_tl := line.new(hoi, high_old, hni, high_new, style = line.style_solid, color = color.gray, width = 1)
            array.set(pivot_highs, 0, na)
            array.set(pivot_highs, 1, na)

// Deviation from range: freeze + recolor the line (delete_old = off), clear the handle.
bool upper_test = false
bool lower_test = false

if not na(upper_tl)
    int   ux2  = line.get_x2(upper_tl)
    float uy2  = line.get_y2(upper_tl)
    float usl  = (uy2 - line.get_y1(upper_tl)) / (ux2 - line.get_x1(upper_tl))
    float proj = uy2 + usl * (bar_index - ux2)
    if high > proj
        line.set_x2(upper_tl, bar_index)
        line.set_y2(upper_tl, proj)
        line.set_color(upper_tl, color.red)
        upper_tl := na
        upper_test := true

if not na(lower_tl)
    int   lx2  = line.get_x2(lower_tl)
    float ly2  = line.get_y2(lower_tl)
    float lsl  = (ly2 - line.get_y1(lower_tl)) / (lx2 - line.get_x1(lower_tl))
    float proj = ly2 + lsl * (bar_index - lx2)
    if low < proj
        line.set_x2(lower_tl, bar_index)
        line.set_y2(lower_tl, proj)
        line.set_color(lower_tl, color.red)
        lower_tl := na
        lower_test := true

plotshape(upper_test, 'BF upper deviation', style = shape.triangledown, color = color.red, size = size.tiny, location = location.abovebar)
plotshape(lower_test, 'BF lower deviation', style = shape.triangleup, color = color.red, size = size.tiny, location = location.belowbar)

// ------------- BF exit orders: resting at the NEXT bar's line projection -------------
f_proj_next(line ln) =>
    float p = na
    if not na(ln)
        int   px2 = line.get_x2(ln)
        float py2 = line.get_y2(ln)
        float psl = (py2 - line.get_y1(ln)) / (px2 - line.get_x1(ln))
        p := py2 + psl * (bar_index + 1 - px2)
    p

float u_next = f_proj_next(upper_tl)
float l_next = f_proj_next(lower_tl)
float bfx_lim = na
float bfx_stp = na

if bf_exit != 'off' and strategy.position_size > 0
    bfx_lim := u_next
    bfx_stp := bf_exit == 'any_side' ? l_next : na
    if not na(bfx_lim) or not na(bfx_stp)
        strategy.exit('BFX-L', from_entry = 'L', limit = bfx_lim, stop = bfx_stp, comment_profit = 'BF upper dev', comment_loss = 'BF lower dev')
    else
        strategy.cancel('BFX-L')
else if bf_exit != 'off' and strategy.position_size < 0
    bfx_lim := l_next
    bfx_stp := bf_exit == 'any_side' ? u_next : na
    if not na(bfx_lim) or not na(bfx_stp)
        strategy.exit('BFX-S', from_entry = 'S', limit = bfx_lim, stop = bfx_stp, comment_profit = 'BF lower dev', comment_loss = 'BF upper dev')
    else
        strategy.cancel('BFX-S')
else
    strategy.cancel('BFX-L')
    strategy.cancel('BFX-S')

// ----------------------------------- Visualization -----------------------------------
barcolor(ftfc_up ? color.new(color.green, 60) : ftfc_dn ? color.new(color.red, 60) : color.new(color.gray, 75))
plot(show_trig and armed > 0 ? eff_trig_l : na, 'Working buy stop', color = color.new(color.orange, 0), style = plot.style_circles, linewidth = 2)
plot(show_trig and armed < 0 ? eff_trig_s : na, 'Working sell stop', color = color.new(color.orange, 0), style = plot.style_circles, linewidth = 2)
plot(not na(bf_block_l) ? bf_block_l : na, 'BF block C (long)', color = color.new(color.teal, 30), style = plot.style_linebr)
plot(not na(bf_block_s) ? bf_block_s : na, 'BF block C (short)', color = color.new(color.maroon, 30), style = plot.style_linebr)
plot(bf_g_dir != 0 ? bf_g_ext : na, 'BF block G extreme', color = color.new(color.purple, 30), style = plot.style_linebr)

f_gates_echo() =>
    string s = ''
    if y1
        s += tf1 + '.'
    if y2
        s += tf2 + '.'
    if y3
        s += tf3 + '.'
    if y4
        s += tf4 + '.'
    if y5
        s += tf5 + '.'
    if y6
        s += tf6 + '.'
    s

string cell_echo = exit_mode + ';' + bf_exit + ';' + bf_reentry + ';a' + arm_tf + ';x' + exit_tf + ';g' + f_gates_echo() + ';d' + (allow_long ? 'L' : '') + (allow_short ? 'S' : '') + ';r' + reg_mode + ';v' + gov_mode

var table t = table.new(position.bottom_right, 2, 9, bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 20), border_width = 1, border_color = color.new(color.gray, 60))
f_cell(int r, string k, string v, color c) =>
    table.cell(t, 0, r, k, text_color = color.white, text_size = size.small, text_halign = text.align_left)
    table.cell(t, 1, r, v, text_color = c, text_size = size.small)

if show_table and barstate.islast
    f_cell(0, 'CELL', exit_mode + '/' + bf_exit + '/' + bf_reentry + ' a' + arm_tf + '/x' + exit_tf, bf_exit != 'off' ? color.orange : color.aqua)
    f_cell(1, 'Gate (live)', ftfc_up ? 'UP' : ftfc_dn ? 'DOWN' : 'GREY', ftfc_up ? color.lime : ftfc_dn ? color.red : color.gray)
    f_cell(2, 'Regime', reg_mode == 'off' ? 'off' : reg_up ? 'UP' : reg_dn ? 'DOWN' : 'GREY', reg_up ? color.lime : reg_dn ? color.red : color.gray)
    f_cell(3, 'Position', strategy.position_size > 0 ? 'LONG' : strategy.position_size < 0 ? 'SHORT' : 'FLAT', strategy.position_size > 0 ? color.lime : strategy.position_size < 0 ? color.red : color.silver)
    f_cell(4, 'BF upper', na(u_next) ? '--' : str.tostring(u_next, format.mintick), color.white)
    f_cell(5, 'BF lower', na(l_next) ? '--' : str.tostring(l_next, format.mintick), color.white)
    f_cell(6, 'Block C L/S | G', (na(bf_block_l) ? '--' : str.tostring(bf_block_l, format.mintick)) + '/' + (na(bf_block_s) ? '--' : str.tostring(bf_block_s, format.mintick)) + ' | ' + (bf_g_dir == 0 ? '--' : str.tostring(bf_g_ext, format.mintick)), color.teal)
    f_cell(7, 'Trades (closed)', str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades), color.white)
    f_cell(8, 'Net profit', str.tostring(strategy.netprofit, format.mintick), strategy.netprofit >= 0 ? color.lime : color.red)

// ----------------- Machine-readable collector echo (transparent tables) -----------------
// GPT-proven integrity method: the collector reads these via pine tables, verifies the
// echoed cell matches the requested cell, and rejects the run otherwise. Cells are fully
// transparent so nothing is drawn over the chart.
var int first_loaded_bar_time = na
if na(first_loaded_bar_time)
    first_loaded_bar_time := time

var table mtab = table.new(position.top_left, 2, 27, bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), frame_color = color.new(color.black, 100))
var table ttab = table.new(position.bottom_left, 1, 61, bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), frame_color = color.new(color.black, 100))

f_mrow(int row, string k, string v) =>
    table.cell(mtab, 0, row, k, text_color = color.new(color.white, 100), bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), text_size = size.tiny)
    table.cell(mtab, 1, row, v, text_color = color.new(color.white, 100), bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), text_size = size.tiny)

// Realtime-bar fix: without calc_on_every_tick a strategy never calculates the live
// realtime bar, and on 24/7 perps a new realtime bar exists within seconds of every
// close -- so `islast` alone leaves these tables UNDRAWN almost always (the root cause
// of the TVB-11 echo-path flakiness). islastconfirmedhistory + a bar_index fallback
// cover every calc pass; later bars simply overwrite, so the final pass wins.
if barstate.islast or barstate.islastconfirmedhistory or bar_index >= last_bar_index - 1
    float long_net = 0.0
    float short_net = 0.0
    float commission_total = 0.0
    if strategy.closedtrades > 0
        for ti = 0 to strategy.closedtrades - 1
            float tp = strategy.closedtrades.profit(ti)
            if strategy.closedtrades.size(ti) > 0
                long_net += tp
            else
                short_net += tp
            commission_total += strategy.closedtrades.commission(ti)
    if strategy.opentrades > 0
        for oi = 0 to strategy.opentrades - 1
            float oc = strategy.opentrades.commission(oi)
            commission_total += oc
            if strategy.opentrades.size(oi) > 0
                long_net -= oc
            else
                short_net -= oc

    int first_entry_ms = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? strategy.closedtrades.entry_time(0) : strategy.opentrades > 0 ? strategy.opentrades.entry_time(0) : na
    int last_event_ms = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? strategy.closedtrades.exit_time(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : na
    if strategy.opentrades > 0
        int oe_ms = strategy.opentrades.entry_time(strategy.opentrades - 1)
        last_event_ms := na(last_event_ms) ? oe_ms : math.max(last_event_ms, oe_ms)

    float pf = strategy.grossloss != 0 ? strategy.grossprofit / math.abs(strategy.grossloss) : na
    float win_rate = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? 100.0 * strategy.wintrades / strategy.closedtrades : na
    float total_net = strategy.netprofit + strategy.openprofit

    f_mrow(0, 'METRICS', 'TVB-EXP Champion [TVB-12r]')
    f_mrow(1, 'cell', cell_echo)
    f_mrow(2, 'symbol', syminfo.tickerid)
    f_mrow(3, 'net_abs', str.tostring(strategy.netprofit))
    f_mrow(4, 'net_pct', str.tostring(100.0 * strategy.netprofit / 10000.0))
    f_mrow(5, 'profit_factor', str.tostring(pf))
    f_mrow(6, 'closed_trades', str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades))
    f_mrow(7, 'win_rate_pct', str.tostring(win_rate))
    f_mrow(8, 'max_dd_pct', str.tostring(strategy.max_drawdown_percent))
    f_mrow(9, 'open_pl_abs', str.tostring(strategy.openprofit))
    f_mrow(10, 'commission', str.tostring(commission_total))
    f_mrow(11, 'long_net', str.tostring(long_net))
    f_mrow(12, 'short_net', str.tostring(short_net))
    f_mrow(13, 'first_entry_ms', str.tostring(first_entry_ms))
    f_mrow(14, 'last_event_ms', str.tostring(last_event_ms))
    f_mrow(15, 'total_net_abs', str.tostring(total_net))
    f_mrow(16, 'total_net_pct', str.tostring(100.0 * total_net / 10000.0))
    f_mrow(17, 'loaded_first_ms', str.tostring(first_loaded_bar_time))
    f_mrow(18, 'loaded_last_ms', str.tostring(time))
    f_mrow(19, 'loaded_bars', str.tostring(bar_index + 1))
    f_mrow(20, 'open_trades', str.tostring(strategy.opentrades))
    f_mrow(21, 'gross_profit_loss', str.tostring(strategy.grossprofit) + ';' + str.tostring(strategy.grossloss))
    // v2 binding rows (audit F1): chart state + BF geometry + the causal nonce.
    f_mrow(22, 'chart_tf', timeframe.period)
    f_mrow(23, 'session', syminfo.session)
    f_mrow(24, 'bf_tf', bf_tf)
    f_mrow(25, 'bf_strength', str.tostring(bf_strength))
    f_mrow(26, 'nonce', coll_nonce)

    // Per-trade rows. 'gross' is the slippage-adjusted price P/L computed from the
    // engine's own entry/exit prices and size -- comparing it to profit() and
    // commission on marginal trades IS the P0b polarity check.
    table.cell(ttab, 0, 0, 'TRADES', text_color = color.new(color.white, 100), bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), text_size = size.tiny)
    for ri = 1 to 60
        table.cell(ttab, 0, ri, '', text_color = color.new(color.white, 100), bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), text_size = size.tiny)
    if strategy.closedtrades > 0
        int tl = math.min(strategy.closedtrades, 60)
        for ti = 0 to tl - 1
            float sz = strategy.closedtrades.size(ti)
            float epx = strategy.closedtrades.entry_price(ti)
            float xpx = strategy.closedtrades.exit_price(ti)
            float gross = (xpx - epx) * sz
            string row = 'i=' + str.tostring(ti)
            row += ';dir=' + (sz > 0 ? 'L' : 'S')
            row += ';entry_ms=' + str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades.entry_time(ti))
            row += ';entry_px=' + str.tostring(epx)
            row += ';exit_ms=' + str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades.exit_time(ti))
            row += ';exit_px=' + str.tostring(xpx)
            row += ';size=' + str.tostring(sz)
            row += ';exit=' + strategy.closedtrades.exit_comment(ti)
            row += ';profit=' + str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades.profit(ti))
            row += ';commission=' + str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades.commission(ti))
            row += ';gross=' + str.tostring(gross)
            table.cell(ttab, 0, ti + 1, row, text_color = color.new(color.white, 100), bgcolor = color.new(color.black, 100), text_size = size.tiny)
